& [ThinkAboutRecord:pressure_impact_001] is a deeper ThinkAbout record over pressure and impact sensitivity signals
  + [focus_signal] is SOP awareness node pressure and impact sensitivity signals
  + [pressure_signal] is sustained signal pressure from changed SOP paths, terms, bookends, evidence, and ThinkAbout candidates
  + [impact_signal] is emphasized signal heat where attention, local authority, scan evidence, and future routing may shape project behavior
  + [evidence] is SensitivityScan recommends pressure and impact as deeper ThinkAbout candidates, SOPAwarenessNode names next_depth as later ThinkAbout or Codex processing, and seed scan records pressure and impact signals with residual outside
  + [triangulation] is pressure asks what should stay noticeable, impact asks what may shape future action, and evidence asks what is actually supported
  + [realization] is pressure and impact form a useful attention handoff only when term correlation remains outside proof and Codex review decides whether a record should become durable
  + [proposal_origin] is pressure_impact_thinkabout_016 retry_001 accepted as proposal evidence after attempt_000 proved external-example drift can pass format validation
  + [integration_status] is Codex-authored record integrated from proposal evidence, not worker-authored integration
  + [caution] is keep task-fit review active because plausible foreign examples can satisfy structure while missing local meaning
  + [next_step] is use this record as the completed Task_003 anchor and select the next safe .sop task under Codex authority
  + [outside] is causal proof, hidden model state, worker mutation authority, broad LM Studio competence, direct trust, external examples, and unresolved deeper runtime work

  = must: keep pressure and impact as attention-routing signals unless additional evidence upgrades them
  = must: cite source evidence before durable integration
  = must: keep accepted worker output as proposal input, not authority
  = should: use this record when deciding whether pressure and impact signals deserve future focus
